com.hp.ov.sdk.rest.http.core.client

Class DownloadPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hp.ov.sdk.rest.http.core.client.DownloadPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RequestOption

    public class DownloadPath
extends Object
implements RequestOption
    Some operations return a file as the entity of a response. In this cases, it is possible to specify a destination folder using an implementation of RequestOption called DownloadPath.

    Once a directory path has been configured, the returned file will be saved in that specific folder.

    If no path is specified, the default behavior is to use the value specified on the SDK configuration (using object SDKConfiguration). Below is an example that shows how the download path can be specified: 

    
     SomeClient client = oneViewClient.someClient();
     SomeResource resource = new SomeResource();
     client.downloadFile(resourceID, new DownloadPath("~/Desktop/"));
